p: Results obtained in the feeding trials can be found in Table 6 and Table 7. The feed conversion ratios of Japanese quail were significantly increased ( p ≤ 0.05) for diets containing B. zonata and S. littoralis meals, respectively, as compared with the control diet containing only soybean meal ( Table 6). The highest feed intake and lowest body weight gain were observed for the control diet as compared to the B. zonata and S. littoralis meals ( p ≤ 0.05). Moreover, significant differences were observed between the B. zonata and S. littoralis meals. The final weight was highest and the feed conversion ratio lowest for the B. zonata meal.
